Server Creation - Nodejs + express

Basic commands
---------------

1) Creating package.json - npm init
2)Creating node modules - npm i express (Installing express)
3)install nodemon - npm install -g nodemon
4)Run - nodemon index.js



Basic steps
-----------

1)Creating a folder (BankServer)
2)Create package.json file
3)Install express
4)Import express inside the index.js file
5)Create an app using express
6)Setup the port number
7)resolving http request

8)HTTP Response code
    1xx-Information
    2xx-successful
    3xx-Redirection
    4xx-client error
    5xx-server error

9)JWT Token 

install JWT Token - npm i jsonwebtoken
To Generate Token - sign()

10)Middleware
It comes in the middle of the request and response cycleon the nodejs execution process
 
     1)Application specific middleware - for entire Application
     req,res,next
     2)Router specific middleware - validate token - verify() -jwtwebtoken

11)Database Integration
    1)Install mongoose - npm i mongoose 
